The whereabouts of a young undergraduate, Azurfa John are currently unknown following the recent terrorist attack on the Kaduna-Abuja train. Azurfa, a 300-level student of Kaduna State University was said to be on the ill-fated train when terrorists struck on Monday, SaharaReporters gathered.  Efforts by family members and friends to reach Azurfa on her mobile phone have proved abortive. She is suspected to be one of the many victims abducted by terrorists. SaharaReporters had reported how terrorists on Monday attacked an Abuja-Kaduna train, killing some of the passengers and abducting an unspecified number of people. On Tuesday, eight persons were confirmed dead and 26 injured.